This is my attempt to solve the very first part of Exercise 3-8 from the O'reilly Erlang Programming book.  This module *should* parse a simple mathematical expression into an erlang data structure.  It does that (save unary negation) but it does so by wrapping each expression and sub expression in a tagged tuple.  The trouble is, I can't seem to unwrap them.

The stack callback object can be initialised with an array of functions which will be performed as soon as trigger() is called. Functions can be push()ed at any time, immediately executing if trigger() has been called. To stop new functions from executing, call stop(). From then on, push()ed functions will be added to the queue array. To remove a function from the queue before it is executed, call remove(). After a function is called, it will be removed from the stack. Requires underscore.js
